00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,700
They stop out of nowhere.

255
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,900
Where did she go?

256
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:22,400
Perhaps she was never even here to begin with.

257
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,400
Look...

258
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,900
Lost colony or not, we have to be prepared

259
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:30,000
for whatever's on the other side of that trail.

260
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,000
Are you all right?

261
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:37,400
Let's keep going.

262
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:45,700
We've got two more patients. Both on the scene when the boy went down.

263
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:49,300
is coming out ???
Are we any closer to knowing where Patient Zero came from?

264
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:52,600
Still searching. We're working on a possible bioterrorism angle.

265
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,500
Looked into a new cult that's surfaced. So far, no link to them.

266
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,600
Why do the others seem more sick than the kid?

267
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,300
People's immune systems react differently.

268
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,600
Some may not be affected. Others may be completely compromised.

269
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:07,100
The vector must come from a very different environment than ours.

270
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:09,800
- Why is that? 
- His blood panels.

271
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:13,900
They show traces of foreign antibodies and a lack of others present in our population.

272
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:17,500
There's no evidence he's ever been vaccinated against anything.

273
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:22,200
To inoculate everyone else against this thing, we need to identify it.

274
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:24,900
We're coming across nothing like it in our database.

275
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:27,700
I have got officers retracing the boy's trail as we speak.

276
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:41,800
This is where Thomas' trail ends.

277
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:45,100
Or... more accurately, begins.

278
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:51,400
I believe the answer to his survival lies somewhere over there.

279
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,300
That tiny island?

280
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,000
There's nothing on it.

281
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,600
Looks can be deceiving, Lieutenant.

282
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:01,900
Perhaps this is how the community has remained hidden.

283
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:03,700
Sure. Maybe.

284
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:07,000
Are you telling me you think the kid swam across this?

285
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,200
No...

286
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:12,500
No, his feet were covered in muck, but not the rest of him.

287
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,200
Okay.

288
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,800
We're gonna have to find another way over there.

289
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:37,600
Crane. Crane!

290
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,900
This is how Thomas made it across.

291
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:46,900
How did you know that?

292
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:51,300
Markings on these trees indicate a hidden crossing.

293
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:55,000
Step this way, Miss Mills.

294
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,400
they have come.

295
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:41,900
What is this place?

296
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,200
where are we?

297
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,800
roanoke

298
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:55,200
Crane... they're all infected.

299
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:13,500
They have the black veins, but don't seem sick.

300
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:16,300
Yes. Quite curious.

301
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:28,900
So this is where Thomas was raised.

302
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:34,900
In a community that hasn't changed in some 400 years.

303
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,500
How is that possible?

304
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:41,400
why did you leave roanoke?

305
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,300
the land of roanoke was cursed...

306
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,800
...by the horseman of pertilence.

307
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:50,400
he rode through one night...

308
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:52,600
...infecting us all.

309
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,800
the youngest among us...

310
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:01,300
...was the first life of many lost.

311
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:02,800
Virginia Dare.

312
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,400
yes

313
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:09,100
shority after her death, her spirit appeared.

314
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:12,000
and lead us away...

315
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,600
...to safety

316
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:18,500
The spirit of Virginia Dare guided the colonists here to protect them.

317
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:21,600
Protect them? But they all have the disease.

318
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:25,100
how are you all well,

319
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:27,600
if you have the same disease Thomas does?

320
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:31,700
its symptoms cannot affect ue here.

321
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:34,600
when Thomas left...

322
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:38,400
...he took the plague with him to the outside.

323
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:45,500
it is what the horseman wanted all alone.

324
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,700
how do we save Thomas?

325
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:51,100
and the others he could infect?

326
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,100
you must return him here.

327
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:57,300
to save them all.

328
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,900
before its too late.

329
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:13,400
The spirit of Virginia Dare seems to watch over them here,

330
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:16,000
keeping their symptoms at bay.

331
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:20,500
Sort of like Katrina putting a spell on you to keep you alive.

332
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:25,700
It seems the colonists of Roanoke and I share much in common.

333
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:31,100
In order to save Thomas, we must bring him back.

334
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:32,900
I'm no Middle English expert,

335
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:36,600
but I could've sworn I heard the word "horseman" thrown in there.

336
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:40,600
Indeed you did, though not the headless one with whom we are acquainted.

337
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,300
The colony was infected with this plague

338
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:47,200
by the Horseman of Pestilence, also known as Conquest.

339
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:50,600
- So another Horseman of the Apocalypse has arrived? 
- Not yet.

340
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,900
And not if we can stop it.

341
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,800
Pestilence instituted this plague centuries ago,

342
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:03,400
stopping its spread and thwarting the Horseman from riding forth.

343
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,800
It's been unleashed anew through Thomas.

344
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,800
If it manages to spread this time...

345
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:14,100
Then the Horseman of Pestilence will come to Sleepy Hollow

346
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,700
and join forces with the Horseman of Death.

347
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:20,000
We must prevent this at all costs.

348
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:24,200
And I think bringing Thomas here will be the answer.

349
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,100
thank you

350
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:32,200
for watching over me son.

351
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:34,300
it is my privilege.

352
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:44,000
No, thank you. You keep it.

353
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,700
Crane.

354
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:57,400
We gotta get going.

355
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:04,500
we shall return with your boy.

356
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:14,000
If what you saw in the Roanoke forest enters our world,

357
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,500
modern medicine will be defenseless against it.

358
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,100
Oh, my God, you're infected.

359
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,900
Be it the protection of Virginia Dare,

360
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:35,100
or something in the environment,

361
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,200
the cure seems to lie within the colony.

362
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:41,500
Maybe, but the CDC is not going to let anyone leave the hospital.

363
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:44,500
And how are we supposed to get them to a place that no one believes exists?

364
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:54,500
It's spreading.

365
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:58,000
Miss Mills... These people are going to die here.

366
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:01,000
Do you think the Roanoke remedy

367
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,600
would even work on people other than Thomas?

368
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,400
Crane?

369
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,600
I've been infected.

370
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:15,800
- It was the colony. - Get me a Hazmat team in here.

371
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:17,900
No. No, I think it was earlier...

372
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,800
When I first encountered Thomas.

373
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:25,100
- We're ready, sir. 
- Get him into quarantine.

374
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:27,000
No. No, I feel perfectly fine.

375
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,500
Listen to him. Don't touch him. Do not take him!

376
00:26:29,500 --> 00:26:32,300
- Stay back, he's contagious. 
- Stop this!

377
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:34,800
- No! I must help Thomas! 
- Sedate him!

378
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,200
No, I just... Please!

379
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,200
No!

380
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:13,200
- Katrina. 
- Ichabod?

381
00:27:13,700 --> 00:27:15,100
Are you really here?

382
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,300
You're not well.

383
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:29,400
- How did you know? 
- Because you're here.

384
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:32,500
But I have been here before.

385
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,100
Only when I've summoned you.

386
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:37,300
I've... I've not been able to for some time.

387
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:40,300
If you are here in any other way...

388
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:43,200
it means that you are dead.

389
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:46,100
Or near to it.

390
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:01,400
Detective Morales.

391
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,700
Yes, hello, Detective.

392
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:05,800
I'm calling from the history department of Oxford's Merton College

393
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:09,100
- regarding your inquiry into a Mr. Ichabod Crane. 
- Yes.

394
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:12,600
He is indeed a tenured professor here, on sabbatical at the moment,

395
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:16,100
and on loan to law enforcement in Westchester County, New York.

396
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:19,400
- I see. 
- Is there any other way I may be of assistance?

397
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,900
No. No, no. Thank you. That's all I needed to know.

398
00:28:24,500 --> 00:28:25,700
Everything okay, Morales?

399
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:27,400
Yes, sir. All good.

400
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:29,500
Track down Parsons from CDC.

401
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:31,800
We need to make a plan to control public response.

402
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,800
Yes, sir.

403
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,500
You must understand.

404
00:28:42,500 --> 00:28:45,500
It's only under great duress you would find yourself here.

405
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:47,800
I am sick.

406
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:50,700
I did not realize how critically.

407
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,300
Another has died from this.

408
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,500
And I fear you will, too.

409
00:28:57,600 --> 00:29:00,600
Ichabod, this place I've been trapped in, it's purgatory.

410
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,800
Purgatory?

411
00:29:04,700 --> 00:29:05,800
Then those are...

412
00:29:06,100 --> 00:29:07,200
Souls.

413
00:29:08,100 --> 00:29:09,600
Who've been collected here.

414
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:13,300
We're all trapped together, and yet very much apart.

415
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:16,000
Those there are moving on.

416
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:18,400
To where?

417
00:29:19,100 --> 00:29:21,000
To wherever he determines.

418
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:23,600
He?

419
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,500
The beast who keeps me captive.

420
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:30,400
Moloch.

421
00:29:35,700 --> 00:29:38,100
Sir, I need a minute.

422
00:29:38,100 --> 00:29:39,000
Don't have one.

423
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:41,900
But it's about Crane and the boy. If you can help me get them out...

424
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:45,000
They're not going anywhere.

425
00:29:45,500 --> 00:29:49,600
We have most of Sleepy Hollow in an absolute panic over this potential epidemic.

426
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:52,400
The doctors will handle the patients. I need you on the streets.

427
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,200
We have to shut down the traffic moving in and out of town.

428
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:56,100
- There is no time for that. 
- My point exactly.

429
00:29:56,100 --> 00:29:58,300
Report to Morales for your post.

430
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:26,200
Really?

431
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:30,700
what the hell.

432
00:30:31,300 --> 00:30:33,400
Why would you be trapped in such a place?

433
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:36,500
What does Moloch want with your soul?

434
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,500
Katrina...

435
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,800
What is it you're not telling me?

436
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,100
If this is a trial...

437
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,800
I'm gonna need a little evidence.

438
00:30:57,900 --> 00:31:00,700
Is that boy really gonna be saved if I get him back to his home?

439
00:31:00,900 --> 00:31:03,400
What about the others? What about Crane?

440
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:04,700
Would he be saved at Roanoke

441
00:31:04,700 --> 00:31:08,700
because it's... trapped in time like him?

442
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:21,300
Show... me... a sign.

443
00:31:22,900 --> 00:31:24,400
Give me something.

444
00:31:27,100 --> 00:31:29,200
Isn't that the kind of thing that you're known for?

445
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:38,800
Yep.

446
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:40,700
Didn't think so.

447
00:31:59,900 --> 00:32:02,000
Something in the environment,

448
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:04,700
the cure seems to lie within the colony.

449
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:21,300
What is it you're afraid to say?

450
00:32:22,300 --> 00:32:24,800
I believe I know why I am here.

451
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:27,400
Why I cannot leave.

452
00:32:28,300 --> 00:32:29,300
Why?

453
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:32,700
Ichabod!

454
00:32:33,300 --> 00:32:34,800
You fight for your life!

455
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:36,500
You fight for the both of us!

456
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:45,400
I need to get them back to the colony.

457
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,000
I think that the springwater there could be what heals them.

458
00:32:49,300 --> 00:32:50,600
Think about it.

459
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:54,700
Water is used in many religions as a way to purify.

460
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:58,700
Roanoke seems to be some sort of holy place.

461
00:32:59,300 --> 00:33:02,500
So you think they need to baptized in it or something?

462
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:03,600
I do.

463
00:33:04,100 --> 00:33:06,600
For now, we're just stalling the inevitable.

464
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:09,400
Thomas will die if he isn't returned. And Crane.

465
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,400
Do you really believe that's going to work?

466
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,500
I've got no choice but to believe.

467
00:33:20,300 --> 00:33:21,300
Okay.

468
00:33:23,500 --> 00:33:25,300
I think I have a way.

469
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:30,400
Another quarantine facility's been set up for projected overflow.

470
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:33,500
Parsons will get orders to transfer Thomas and Crane there,

471
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:36,800
creating an opportunity for you to get them to this colony.

472
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,200
I'll cover for you.

473
00:33:38,500 --> 00:33:40,500
If the solution is there, I'll do what I can

474
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:42,900
to get the remaining infected to the location.

475
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:46,100
But, Abbie... Hurry.

476
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:49,400
Hey, what are you doing?!

477
00:33:53,300 --> 00:33:54,800
Keep talking to me, Crane.

478
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,900
Keep your mind off the pain.

479
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:02,400
Katrina. I saw Katrina while I was unconscious.

480
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:05,700
And now I understand why I haven't been able to go there.

481
00:34:05,900 --> 00:34:06,900
Why?

482
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,600
The place is...

483
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:12,000
is a purgatory

484
00:34:12,900 --> 00:34:16,100
for souls left hanging in the balance,

485
00:34:16,100 --> 00:34:18,100
caught between good and evil.

486
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:22,800
It's like a no-man's-land on a battlefield.

487
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:26,400
I'm glad you fought your way out of it.

488
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:28,200
Crane!

489
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:29,400
I'm all right.

490
00:34:30,500 --> 00:34:32,100
I can't say the same for Thomas.

491
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:35,200
We're losing him.

492
00:34:50,500 --> 00:34:52,400
It's weak, but he's still got a heartbeat.

493
00:34:53,200 --> 00:34:55,400
We've got to keep moving. Almost there.

494
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:59,400
I'm so sorry. I feel a little faint.

495
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:05,100
You go on to Roanoke. Send the colonists back for us.

496
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:07,000
I cannot make it without you.

497
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:09,800
- Yes, you can. 
- All the trees look the same to me.

498
00:35:10,100 --> 00:35:11,100
Hang on.

499
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:12,600
I need a little rest.

500
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:13,100
Hang on.

501
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:17,600
I think you just need a little, a little boost.

502
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:25,100
What was that?

503
00:35:25,100 --> 00:35:26,100
Adrenaline.

504
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:28,100
I like it.

505
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:33,700
Let's keep moving.

506
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:46,200
Crane!

507
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:49,300
Get to the water! Run!

508
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,200
Crane!

509
00:36:03,300 --> 00:36:04,300
Hurry!

510
00:36:04,700 --> 00:36:06,400
Crane! Crane!

511
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:18,200
You were right.

512
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,900
The waters provide a cure.

513
00:36:38,900 --> 00:36:40,000
What just happened?

514
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:44,300
Thomas...

515
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:51,700
He was dead all along. They all were.

516
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:00,900
But everyone else in Sleepy Hollow, they saw him.

517
00:37:01,300 --> 00:37:02,800
They were affected by him.

518
00:37:03,300 --> 00:37:05,400
He returned to flesh and blood...

519
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:10,000
once he was lured into our world to spread a plague.

520
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,200
But we stopped it.

521
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:14,100
Somehow.

522
00:37:14,100 --> 00:37:16,600
You stopped it by having faith.

523
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:22,000
